<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>xi blog</title><link href="/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="/feeds/sublime-text.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>/</id><updated>2015-11-09T00:00:00+03:00</updated><entry><title>Custom Sublime Text build system for python on Fedora 22</title><link href="/custom-sublime-text-build-system-for-python-on-fedora-22.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-11-09T00:00:00+03:00</updated><author><name>xi</name></author><id>tag:,2015-11-09:custom-sublime-text-build-system-for-python-on-fedora-22.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;We need to configure custom build system in Sublime Text. The main requirement is possibility to execute code in new window.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let's create new build system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tools &amp;gt; Build System &amp;gt; New Build System...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Configuration is below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;cmd&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;gnome-terminal&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;-x&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;bash&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;-c&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;python $file; read&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;],&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# run new terminal&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;shell&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="sublime text"></category><category term="build system"></category></entry></feed>